This vacancy is a FLEX in 2-Shift position within the group “TF CL Service Lab Operations” and main task is the operations of reticles in the Service Lab for the Twinscan & EUV factory. In the Service Lab wafers and reticles are prepared for exposure, processed after exposure, measured and recycled. The operator is responsible to process requests for internal customers as well as for the field. The operator reports to the Team leader and has interfaces with delivery operations, development, customer support, equipment support and the direct colleague technicians and engineers.

Functie
Responsible for the processing of reticle requests for internal customers as well as for the field with the right quality;
Working with and monitors the reticle tooling and supporting measurement equipment in the Reticle Lab.
Works closely with the technicians and engineers in the Service Lab.
Working closely with the Service Lab Pellicle Workcenter
Willing to work 80% behind a computer;
Analysis and solving of minor disturbances as well as escalation of major disturbances;
Plan and prioritize own work; report, inform and escalate correctly and timely on progress and status;
